e accent systems, where the occurrence of contrastive tonal melodies is restricted to stressed syllables. The volume has an empirical emphasis on Franconian dialects in the Netherlands, Belgium and Germany, but also discusses languages as diverse as Slovenian, Livonian, Fuzhou Chinese, and Xhosa.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aConsonants. 0aIntonation (Phonetics). 0aPhoneticsxResearch. 0aProsodic analysis (Linguistics). 0aSonorants (Phonetics). 0aTone (Phonetics). 0aVowels. 4aPhonologie. 4aProsodie. 4aTonalität. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aPhonology.  aProsody.  aTone.1 aBecker, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoersma, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoersma, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDonohue, Cathryn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDowning, Laura J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJurgec, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKehrein, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKehrein, Wolfgang, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKiparsky, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKöhnlein, Björn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKöhnlein, Björn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOostendorp, Marc van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOostendorp, Marc, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z9783110762495